      "type": "LinguisticObject",
      "content": "An oil painting on panel (63 x 81 cm) by **Wybrand Hendriks** (Amsterdam, 1744 – Haarlem, 1831), dated 1799, depicting a session of the **Haarlemse Teekencollegie** — the private drawing society that Hendriks himself founded in 1796 as successor to the dissolved *Haarlemse Stads Teekenacademie* (1772–1795). Members are shown drawing from plaster casts of classical antiquities (Venus de Medici, Venus Callipyge, Apollo Belvedere, and a Vulcan's forge group). Hendriks appears at far right. Six figures are named in the catalog: van Brussel, Visser Bender, Claterbos, Milatz, van der Willigen, Gerlings. Donated to Teylers in 1987 by Mrs. J.H.M. Staring-de Mol van Otterloo. Exhibited in the major 2023 Teylers retrospective *\"Wybrand Hendriks was hier!\"*. Designated one of Teylers' **50 Topstukken**.",
